-- Serbian Police Recover $131 Million Cezanne Painting
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-04-12T09:12:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/serbian-police-recover-131-million-cezanne-painting.html
Serbian police recovered a painting
by Paul Cezanne that was stolen four years ago, Blic newspaper
 reported , without saying where it obtained the information.  Three suspects were arrested during raids in Belgrade and
Cacak, in southern  Serbia , the newspaper said.  The painting, “Boy in the Red Vest,” was stolen from a
museum in Zurich, Switzerland, along with works by Edgar Degas,
Vincent Van Gogh and Claude Monet.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  